data.content:
This is a well-known set of breaking changes. .NET 10's `Microsoft.AspNetCore.OpenApi` upgraded from **Microsoft.OpenApi v1 → v2**, which aligns with **OpenAPI 3.1 / JSON Schema**. Here's what changed and the fixed code:

### Key changes

| v1 (.NET 9) | v2 (.NET 10) | Why |
|---|---|---|
| `Microsoft.OpenApi.Any.OpenApiString` | `System.Text.Json.Nodes.JsonValue` | OpenAPI 3.1 uses raw JSON, not custom wrapper types |
| `schema.Nullable = true/false` | `schema.Type \|= JsonSchemaType.Null` | OpenAPI 3.1 models nullable via the `type` array, not a separate flag |
| `new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "..." }` | `new OpenApiReference("oauth2")` | `OpenApiReference` simplified — it now takes the `Id` directly; `Type` is inferred from context |
| `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { [scheme] = scopes }` | `new OpenApiSecurityRequirement { Scheme = scheme, Scopes = scopes }` | No longer a dictionary; uses explicit `Scheme`/`Scopes` properties |

### Fixed code

```csharp
using System.Text.Json.Nodes;        // replaces Microsoft.OpenApi.Any
using Microsoft.OpenApi.Models;

options.AddOperationTransformer((operation, context, ct) =>
{
    var param = operation.Parameters.FirstOrDefault(p => p.Name == "api-version");
    if (param is not null)
    {
        param.Schema.Example = JsonValue.Create("1.0");          // was: new OpenApiString("1.0")
    }

    operation.Responses.TryAdd("401", new OpenApiResponse { Description = "Unauthorized" });

    var oAuthScheme = new OpenApiSecurityScheme
    {
        Reference = new OpenApiReference("oauth2")               // was: new OpenApiReference { Type = ReferenceType.SecurityScheme, Id = "oauth2" }
    };
    operation.Security = new List<OpenApiSecurityRequirement>
    {
        new() { Scheme = oAuthScheme, Scopes = scopes }          // was: new() { [oAuthScheme] = scopes }
    };

    return Task.CompletedTask;
});

options.AddSchemaTransformer((schema, context, ct) =>
{
    if (schema.Properties is not null)
    {
        foreach (var property in schema.Properties)
        {
            if (schema.Required?.Contains(property.Key) != true)
                property.Value.Type &= ~JsonSchemaType.Null;     // was: property.Value.Nullable = false
        }
    }
    return Task.CompletedTask;
});
```

### Summary of changes

1. **`OpenApiString` → `JsonValue.Create()`** — all `OpenApi*` primitive types are gone; use `System.Text.Json.Nodes` instead.
2. **`OpenApiReference`** — constructor now takes the reference ID directly; type is inferred from where it's used.
3. **`OpenApiSecurityRequirement`** — no longer a dictionary; set `Scheme` and `Scopes` properties.
4. **`Nullable`** — removed entirely; nullable is now expressed by including `JsonSchemaType.Null` in the `Type` flags enum. Use `&= ~JsonSchemaType.Null` to remove it or `|= JsonSchemaType.Null` to add it.
